UBS AG (UBSN)  plans to sell contingent
capital notes in dollars this week, according to two people with
knowledge of the sale.  The dollar-denominated notes will mature in February 2022
and are callable from February 2017, the people said. The
securities are permanently written down if the bankâ€™s capital
falls below a certain level.  BNP Paribas SA, Commerzbank AG, Deutsche Bank AG and
Societe Generale SA are managing the deal with UBS.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
